{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-04-08T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Water spills in clean lines at Sgwd yr Eira, one of South Wales' most distinctive waterfalls. Its Welsh name means 'Waterfall of Snow,' referring to the pale curtain of water sliding over the rock face. What sets this waterfall apart is access. A narrow path leads visitors behind the falling water, immersing them in sound, light and movement at close range. Sgwd yr Eira lies within Brecon Beacons National Park, often called 'Waterfall Country' for its network of rivers and falls carved into wooded gorges. Well-marked trails connect this waterfall to others along the River Hepste, making it a popular stop on longer hikes. Above the valleys, the landscape opens into rolling moorland and long ridgelines where upland paths are shaped by wind and changing weather. These contrasts define the Brecon Beacons, where open, exposed uplands give way to sheltered water, tying the landscape together.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.WalesWaterfall_EN-IN1569227475_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.WalesWaterfall_EN-IN1569227475_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Veil of light","Title":"Sgwd yr Eira waterfall, Brecon Beacons National Park, Wales","Copyright":"© Guy Edwardes/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/51.78174,-3.554824/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=51.78174,-3.554824;S9;Sgwd yr Eira waterfall, Brecon Beacons National Park, Wales&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260409_WalesWaterfall\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Brecon+Beacons+National+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260408_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260409_WalesWaterfall"},"Ssd":"20260409","Name":"WalesWaterfall","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"1569227475","FullDateString":"9 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Seattle's waterfront seems suspended between sea and sky as soft light settles on the horizon. The city in Washington, United States, is named after Chief Si'ahl, a leader of the Duwamish and Suquamish peoples, whose legacy remains important to the region's identity. Steep streets lead down to piers that sweep across Elliott Bay. Rising above the shoreline, the Space Needle stands out as the city's most recognisable landmark. Pike Place Market, founded in 1907, overlooks the waterfront and continues to anchor daily life and long-held traditions.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SeattleSunrise_EN-IN1391422222_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SeattleSunrise_EN-IN1391422222_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The Emerald City","Title":"Seattle, Washington, United States","Copyright":"© Jim Patterson/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/47.60323,-122.330276/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=47.60323,-122.330276;S9;Seattle, Washington, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260408_SeattleSunrise\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Seattle&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260407_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260408_SeattleSunrise"},"Ssd":"20260408","Name":"SeattleSunrise","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"1391422222","FullDateString":"8 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Sea anemones may look like underwater flowers, but they're actually animals—close relatives of jellyfish and corals. Anchored to rocks or reefs, they use a sticky base and a crown of waving tentacles armed with tiny stingers to capture passing prey. Those stings can paralyse small fish, yet one famous neighbour is immune.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OcellarisClownfish_EN-IN1152151443_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OcellarisClownfish_EN-IN1152151443_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Reefside roommates","Title":"Common clownfish in a sea anemone, Raja Ampat Islands, Indonesia","Copyright":"© Magnus Lundgren/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-0.233312,130.507889/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-0.233312,130.507889;S9;Raja Ampat Islands, Southwest Papua, Indonesia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260407_OcellarisClownfish\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sea+anemone&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260406_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260407_OcellarisClownfish"},"Ssd":"20260407","Name":"OcellarisClownfish","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"1152151443","FullDateString":"7 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Picture northern Japan in the early 1600s. Castles stood at the crossroads of politics, trade and governance. Across generations, they came to reflect not only moments of tension, but also endurance, adaptation and everyday life. Castle Day, celebrated on April 6, was created to highlight that layered past. The day uses a simple phonetic link—shi (4) and ro (6)—to form Shiro-no-Hi, because 'shiro' means castle in Japanese. It's a reminder that castles had serious jobs long before they had cinematic appeal.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.CastleBlossoms_EN-IN0940627111_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.CastleBlossoms_EN-IN0940627111_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Where power resides","Title":"Hirosaki Castle with cherry blossoms, Hirosaki, Japan","Copyright":"© Glenn Waters/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/40.609463,140.467545/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=40.609463,140.467545;S9;Hirosaki Castle, Hirosaki, Japan&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260406_CastleBlossoms\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Japanese+castle&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260405_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260406_CastleBlossoms"},"Ssd":"20260406","Name":"CastleBlossoms","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"0940627111","FullDateString":"6 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What follows 40 days of waiting is not a spectacle, but a chapter rooted in belief. Easter Sunday arrives at the end of Lent, carrying forward ideas of life over death and the promise of renewal. For Christians, today marks the resurrection of Jesus Christ and brings Holy Week to a close. It's a turning point, both spiritual and symbolic.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LithuaniaEggs_EN-IN6625019465_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LithuaniaEggs_EN-IN6625019465_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Hello, Easter Sunday","Title":"Colourful handmade wooden Easter eggs, Vilnius, Lithuania","Copyright":"© maximkabb/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Easter Sunday marks the end of the 40-day Lenten season of fasting, prayer and penance.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260405_LithuaniaEggs\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Easter+Sunday&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260404_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260405_LithuaniaEggs"},"Ssd":"20260405","Name":"LithuaniaEggs","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"6625019465","FullDateString":"5 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Before sunrise, the moorland clock punches in—and the dance floor opens. Male black grouse don't send invites; they boom them. Welcome to lekking season, where romance is competitive, noisy and strictly outdoors.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GrouseGuff_EN-IN5681124078_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GrouseGuff_EN-IN5681124078_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The lek side story","Title":"Black grouse males facing off on a lekking site, Estonia","Copyright":"© Sven Zacek/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Black grouse males have a striking, bright red wattle (skin) above their eyes, which they inflate during mating displays.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260404_GrouseGuff\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Black+grouse&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260403_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260404_GrouseGuff"},"Ssd":"20260404","Name":"GrouseGuff","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"5681124078","FullDateString":"4 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Some bridges in Amsterdam just get you across a canal. The Armbrug does more—it seems to wave hello as you pass. Nestled over the Oudezijds Voorburgwal canal, its name, meaning 'arm bridge,' refers to the nearby Oudezijds Armsteeg (Old Side Arm Alley), not a literal limb, but it's easy to imagine it greeting cyclists and pedestrians along the way.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ArmbrugBridge_EN-IN5224260925_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ArmbrugBridge_EN-IN5224260925_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Bridging the gap, one arm at a time","Title":"Armbrug bridge, Amsterdam, Netherlands","Copyright":"© Alexander Spatari/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/52.375378,4.900051/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=52.375378,4.900051;S9;Oudezijds Armsteeg & Oudezijds Voorburgwal Canal Bridge, Amsterdam, Netherlands&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260403_ArmbrugBridge\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Armbrug+bridge+Amsterdam&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260402_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260403_ArmbrugBridge"},"Ssd":"20260403","Name":"ArmbrugBridge","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"5224260925","FullDateString":"3 Apr, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Each spring, Washington's Skagit Valley transforms into a patchwork of colour as the Skagit Valley Tulip Festival celebrates the arrival of bloom season. Throughout April, visitors can explore tulip gardens and farmland lined with vibrant rows of flowers, all framed by mountain views.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_EN-IN3934438603_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_EN-IN3934438603_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Petal parade","Title":"Skagit Valley Tulip Fields, Washington, United States","Copyright":"© Alan Majchrowicz/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/48.5,-122.033/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=48.5,-122.033;S9;Skagit Valley, Washington, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Skagit+Valley+Washington&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260415_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips"},"Ssd":"20260416","Name":"SkagitTulips","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"3934438603","FullDateString":"16 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Art surrounds us. Creativity and self-expression are part of human identity and mould our past and future. While some might dedicate their lives to the arts, others are the recipients of what artists channel. World Art Day on April 15 celebrates this ever-flowing link between artistic creations and society that shapes our cultures.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.VanGoghFields_EN-IN6304322280_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.VanGoghFields_EN-IN6304322280_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"Stepping inside the living canvas","Title":"The Carrières des Lumières exhibit of Vincent van Gogh, Les Baux-de-Provence, France","Copyright":"© Patrick Aventurier/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"World Art Day is held on 15 April to mark the birthday of Leonardo da Vinci, honouring his lasting influence on art and human creativity.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260415_VanGoghFields\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Art+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260414_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260415_VanGoghFields"},"Ssd":"20260415","Name":"VanGoghFields","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"6304322280","FullDateString":"15 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Every year on April 14, India pauses to honour a man who drafted more than just a constitution—he drafted the blueprint for social justice. Ambedkar Jayanti celebrates Dr. B.R. Ambedkar, a scholar, reformer and relentless champion of equality. Born in 1891, Ambedkar faced the harsh realities of caste discrimination but turned every hurdle into a stepping stone for change.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AmbedkarJayanti2026_EN-IN3641683791_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AmbedkarJayanti2026_EN-IN3641683791_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Not just a birthday, a revolution","Title":"Ambedkar Memorial Park, Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh","Copyright":"© Varun Kumar Tiwari/iStock/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/26.849377,80.976776/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=26.849377,80.976776;S9;Ambedkar Memorial Park, Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260414_AmbedkarJayanti2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Ambedkar+Jayanti&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260413_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260414_AmbedkarJayanti2026"},"Ssd":"20260414","Name":"AmbedkarJayanti2026","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"3641683791","FullDateString":"14 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"When the lights go down, the universe puts on a show. International Dark Sky Week, celebrated each April, invites everyone to rediscover the night and learn why darkness is worth protecting. Launched in 2003, the week highlights how excessive artificial light affects wildlife, human health, energy use and our ability to see the stars. Fewer lights don't mean less safety—smart, well-designed lighting can do both.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BorregoStars_EN-IN2846815950_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BorregoStars_EN-IN2846815950_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"After the lights go down","Title":"Milky Way over Anza-Borrego Desert State Park, California, United States","Copyright":"© Kevin Key/Slworking)/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/33.100494,-116.301331/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=33.100494,-116.301331;S9;Anza-Borrego Desert State Park, Borrego Springs, California, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260413_BorregoStars\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Dark+Sky+Week&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260412_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260413_BorregoStars"},"Ssd":"20260413","Name":"BorregoStars","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2846815950","FullDateString":"13 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today, the world marks the International Day of Human Space Flight, a United Nations observance honouring the first human journey into space and the start of the space age for humanity. The date recalls 12 April, 1961, when Yuri Gagarin orbited Earth, proving that people could leave the planet and return safely.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpaceTrails_EN-IN2633640541_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpaceTrails_EN-IN2633640541_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The first step off Earth","Title":"City lights streak below, taken from the International Space Station","Copyright":"© NASA","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"The UN established the International Day of Human Space Flight in 2011, 50 years after the first human spaceflight.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260412_SpaceTrails\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Day+of+Human+Space+Flight&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260411_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260412_SpaceTrails"},"Ssd":"20260412","Name":"SpaceTrails","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2633640541","FullDateString":"12 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A beach born from fire rarely does so subtly, yet Papagayo Beach manages exactly that. The shoreline we see today rests on the southern edge of Lanzarote, one of Spain's Canary Islands. Tropical fantasy? More like volcanic precision. Millions of years ago, this land rose in successive layers of basalt and ash thrust upward by submarine eruptions.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PlayaPapagayo_EN-IN2411013538_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PlayaPapagayo_EN-IN2411013538_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Volcanic veneer","Title":"Papagayo Beach, Lanzarote, Canary Islands, Spain","Copyright":"© Gavin Hellier/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/28.84295,-13.78824/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=28.84295,-13.78824;S9;Playa del Papagayo, Lanzarote, Canary Islands, Spain&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260411_PlayaPapagayo\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lanzarote+Canary+Islands+Spain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260410_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260411_PlayaPapagayo"},"Ssd":"20260411","Name":"PlayaPapagayo","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2411013538","FullDateString":"11 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Ever caught siblings plotting? In Karula National Park, Estonia, it looks as though these two red fox kits froze mid-conspiracy, their expressions mirrored in curiosity and caution. They're not just springtime fluff; they're apprentices in survival. Born in litters averaging four to six kits, foxes grow quickly, their underground den becoming their wrestling ring, classroom, and testing ground. Older kits often help feed, guard, and teach the younger ones, turning play into practice and mischief into muscle memory. In their families, siblings are not background—they're backup.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.FoxSiblings_EN-IN1951935452_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.FoxSiblings_EN-IN1951935452_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Plotting paws","Title":"Two young red foxes at Karula National Park, Estonia","Copyright":"© Sven Zacek/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/57.714678,26.486612/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=57.714678,26.486612;S9;Karula National Park, Rebasemoisa, Estonia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260410_FoxSiblings\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl